    "body": "## Problem\r\nErrors from semantic token requests were getting logged even though the RPC layer already logs them before calling the callback, making these error log messages redundant.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nRemove redundant logging in the semantic tokens layer and leave the rpc layer logging as the goto source for debugging issues.\r\n\r\nFixes #40208",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-15T19:34:43Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I don't think we should remove this information. The RPC layer log records all traffic at the DEBUG level, including both errors and normal messages. In contrast, the LSP layer log only records explicit errors originating from the LSP server, and these are all at the ERROR level. In this regard, semantic tokens should not be treated differently from other LSP modules.\n\nBy checking the message codes in the error messages, we can rule out RPC layer errors being logged at the LSP layer. However, this still doesn't resolve #40208, because it is indeed an explicit LSP layer error returned by the LSP server.",
            "created_at": "2026-06-15T13:02:32Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40269#issuecomment-4708190051",
            "id": 4708190051,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/40269",
