            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> deduping doesn't quite make sense because each of these errors is from a different request\r\n\r\nif we know that `code = -32801, message = \"Content modified.\"` is a noisy request, surely we can be smarter about it. log it once and include a hint like \"this will only be logged once\".\r\n\r\nbut if we are sure this is a LS bug then reporting it to the LS also makes sense, because the RPC logs will still be very noisy even if we dedupe at a higher layer.",
